@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div style="margin: 20px 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;">
    <h2>OCPI EMSP Simulator - Privacy Policy</h2>

    <h3>1. Overview</h3>
    <p>
        The OCPI EMSP Simulator ("Application") is a development and testing tool designed to simulate 
        Electric Mobility Service Provider (EMSP) behavior for OCPI (Open Charge Point Interface) 2.3 
        protocol testing and integration development.
    </p>

    <h3>2. Data Collection and Processing</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>Local Data Storage Only:</strong>
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>All data is stored locally in SQLite database</li>
        <li>No data is transmitted to external servers or cloud services</li>
        <li>No telemetry, tracking, or analytics are collected</li>
        <li>No personal information is collected or processed</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Data Types Stored Locally</h3>
    <p>
        The Application may store the following technical data for OCPI protocol simulation:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>CPO (Charge Point Operator) connection configuration and credentials</li>
        <li>OCPI authentication tokens for handshake testing</li>
        <li>Raw OCPI protocol payloads (request/response messages)</li>
        <li>Credential exchange logs and audit trails</li>
        <li>Error simulation flags for testing error scenarios</li>
        <li>Timestamps of OCPI transactions</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4. Data Scope</h3>
    <p>
        This data is intended to be:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Test Data Only:</strong> Not representative of real users or transactions</li>
        <li><strong>Development-Use:</strong> For protocol testing and integration verification</li>
        <li><strong>Non-Production:</strong> Should not be used with live production systems</li>
        <li><strong>Isolated:</strong> Never shared with third parties</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5. User Access and Control</h3>
    <p>
        Users have full control over all stored data:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Direct access to SQLite database</li>
        <li>Ability to delete or modify all records</li>
        <li>Option to reset error simulation flags at any time</li>
        <li>View complete audit trail of all operations</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>6. Security Considerations</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>Important:</strong> This is a development tool and is NOT intended for production use.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>No encryption of stored data (SQLite default)</li>
        <li>No authentication on internal UI endpoints</li>
        <li>No authorization controls on data access</li>
        <li>Should only be deployed in isolated development environments</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>7. OCPI Token Handling</h3>
    <p>
        Tokens used for OCPI protocol testing:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Are stored in plain text in local SQLite database</li>
        <li>Are masked in UI display (first 4 and last 4 characters only)</li>
        <li>Should be test tokens only, never production credentials</li>
        <li>Can be revoked and cleared via the Handshake page</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>8. Payload Storage</h3>
    <p>
        Raw OCPI payloads are stored verbatim for protocol compliance testing:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Request and response bodies captured in full</li>
        <li>Stored as plain text JSON</li>
        <li>Used for debugging and interoperability verification</li>
        <li>Can be inspected via the Logs page</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>9. Data Retention</h3>
    <p>
        Data is retained indefinitely until:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>User manually deletes database records</li>
        <li>User deletes the SQLite database file</li>
        <li>Application instance is reset</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>10. Third-Party Services</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>No Third-Party Data Sharing:</strong>
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>The Application does not use external APIs or cloud services for core functionality</li>
        <li>External CPO connections are initiated by the user (outbound calls only)</li>
        <li>User is responsible for compliance with external CPO privacy policies</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>11. Error Simulation and Testing</h3>
    <p>
        The Application includes deterministic error simulation for testing purposes:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Simulated 401 Unauthorized and 403 Forbidden errors</li>
        <li>Flags are persisted to database</li>
        <li>Used for testing error handling in client applications</li>
        <li>Errors are completely controllable and reversible</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>12. User Responsibilities</h3>
    <p>
        Users are responsible for:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Using the Application only in development/test environments</li>
        <li>Not connecting to production CPO systems without explicit permission</li>
        <li>Keeping test credentials separate from production credentials</li>
        <li>Ensuring compliance with OCPI specification requirements</li>
        <li>Protecting the database file in case it contains sensitive test data</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>13. Compliance Notes</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>GDPR/Privacy Regulations:</strong>
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>This Application does not process personal data by design</li>
        <li>Test tokens and configurations should not contain personal information</li>
        <li>If personal data is included, users are responsible for compliance</li>
        <li>The Application itself makes no external data transmissions</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>14. Open Source Information</h3>
    <p>
        This Application is open-source software available on GitHub:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Source code is publicly available for inspection</li>
        <li>No hidden data collection mechanisms</li>
        <li>Community-driven development</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>15. Changes to Privacy Policy</h3>
    <p>
        This privacy policy may be updated to reflect changes in the Application. 
        Users will be notified of significant changes.
    </p>

    <h3>16. Contact and Support</h3>
    <p>
        For questions about this privacy policy or the Application, please refer to the 
        project documentation and issue tracker on GitHub.
    </p>

    <div style="margin-top: 30px; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #007bff; background-color: #e7f3ff;">
        <p style="margin: 0;">
            <strong>Summary:</strong> The OCPI EMSP Simulator is a local development tool that stores all data 
            locally in SQLite with no external data transmission. It is designed for protocol testing and 
            integration development only, and should not be used with production systems or real user data.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
